00:41.805 --> 00:44.223
♪

01:00.540 --> 01:04.360
HEATHER: Is that her?
Is that Cat?

01:04.361 --> 01:05.527
Stay in the car.

01:05.529 --> 01:07.496
HEATHER:
Wait! Evan...!

01:08.548 --> 01:10.716
(growls softly)

01:11.835 --> 01:12.718
(growls softly)

01:12.720 --> 01:14.337
NYPD!

01:14.339 --> 01:16.339
Who's out there?

01:22.846 --> 01:25.181
Cat... Cat, can you hear me?

01:25.183 --> 01:28.734
Oh, my God...
Oh, my God.

01:32.222 --> 01:33.555
Heather, I need you!

01:36.326 --> 01:38.744
HEATHER (crying):
Cat...!

01:39.729 --> 01:41.113
Oh, my God!

01:41.115 --> 01:42.531
Oh, my God! Is she okay?

01:42.533 --> 01:45.117
She is bleeding
everywhere.

01:45.119 --> 01:46.952
That's the least of her problems.
She's barely breathing.

01:46.954 --> 01:48.348
What?!

01:48.373 --> 01:49.956
Decreased inhalation
on the right side.

01:50.415 --> 01:51.660
Well, then get
her to a hospital.

01:51.661 --> 01:53.661
She won't make it to a hospital.
Her lung is collapsing.

01:53.663 --> 01:55.463
I need you to go
back to the car,

01:55.465 --> 01:57.515
get that flask of
vodka that you had.

01:57.517 --> 01:59.166
I need a knife, and a glove,
and a rubber band.

01:59.168 --> 02:01.669
Okay...

02:01.671 --> 02:04.305
You're going to be
all right, okay?

02:04.307 --> 02:05.339
Just hang in there.

02:05.341 --> 02:07.675
Just stay with me,
all right?

02:09.695 --> 02:10.862
(car door shuts)

02:14.483 --> 02:15.733
Come on, Heather!

02:17.870 --> 02:19.203
Here, here, here.

02:19.205 --> 02:20.989
Great. That's great.
Well done.

02:20.991 --> 02:22.740
Okay...
Okay, this is the compress.

02:22.742 --> 02:24.158
Give me your hand. Give it here.
What?!

02:24.160 --> 02:26.377
Put pressure on it,
and hold down.

02:26.379 --> 02:27.795
Keep holding it down.

02:27.797 --> 02:30.164
Okay.
We can't let any more air get in.

02:30.166 --> 02:32.366
I think I saw something
in the trees.

02:33.836 --> 02:35.503
There's nothing out there.

02:35.505 --> 02:38.006
Just stay focused, okay?

02:38.008 --> 02:40.174
Everything's
going to be fine.

02:40.176 --> 02:42.543
(crying)

02:42.545 --> 02:45.713
You're doing great;
just keep that pressure on.

02:45.715 --> 02:47.648
I'm going to replace that
with this glove, all right?

02:47.650 --> 02:49.017
Now keep the
pressure down on that.

02:59.394 --> 03:00.695
Okay...

03:08.954 --> 03:11.255
Wha-wha...?
Trust me.

03:11.257 --> 03:12.073
(puncturing)

03:18.547 --> 03:20.748
Okay, Heather.
Breathe.

03:22.217 --> 03:24.218
(labored gasp)

03:25.521 --> 03:27.055
Breathe...

03:28.423 --> 03:30.758
That's it.
That's it.

03:32.811 --> 03:34.529
That's it.
(anxious sigh)

03:34.531 --> 03:36.931
(weak exhale)

03:37.816 --> 03:39.200
She's going to be fine.

03:39.202 --> 03:41.202
Okay, you need to
call 911, tell them

03:41.204 --> 03:43.704
you have an officer down
with a bullet wound, okay?

03:43.706 --> 03:45.773
We need a Medevac to
New York General immediately.

03:47.726 --> 03:51.779
(weak, labored breathing)

03:51.781 --> 03:54.248
Just keep breathing.

03:54.250 --> 03:56.451
(siren wails in distance)

03:57.419 --> 04:00.088
(siren continues,
getting closer)

04:19.992 --> 04:21.976
NURSE (distant, echoing):
Hey, you're awake.

04:21.978 --> 04:24.612
(echoing fades): Don't worry...
it's all going to be fine.

04:25.447 --> 04:28.916
I have... no idea where I am.

04:28.918 --> 04:30.835
New York General.

04:30.837 --> 04:33.304
You were
Medevac'd in last night.

04:34.790 --> 04:36.557
First-timer, I take it.

04:37.876 --> 04:40.511
Well, I called and said
the other bed was broken,

04:40.513 --> 04:42.797
so you could have
some peace and quiet.

04:42.799 --> 04:44.765
Thank you.

04:44.767 --> 04:47.301
Don't really need any
crazy roommates right now.

04:47.303 --> 04:51.622
Speaking of, um...
have you seen my sister?

04:51.624 --> 04:53.691
A small version of you,
teetering around on heels,

04:53.693 --> 04:54.775
reeking of vodka?

04:54.777 --> 04:56.611
Sounds about right.

04:56.613 --> 04:58.312
She wouldn't
leave your side.

04:58.314 --> 05:00.848
I finally gave her a
banana bag for her hangover

05:00.850 --> 05:02.483
and sent her home to sleep.

05:04.620 --> 05:06.520
You did great in surgery.

05:06.522 --> 05:08.105
Both of them.

05:08.107 --> 05:10.458
Both?
What are you talking about?

05:10.460 --> 05:14.145
The police said you crawled out
of a mangled car.

05:14.147 --> 05:17.048
Apparently, some do-gooder
doctor found you,

05:17.050 --> 05:19.550
performed a needle thoracostomy
on you in the field,

05:19.552 --> 05:21.002
with a pocket knife.

05:21.004 --> 05:23.838
If it wasn't for him,
you'd be dead.

05:26.675 --> 05:29.427
And I'm guessing from that
look, you know who he is.

05:30.879 --> 05:32.563
He must be special.

05:32.565 --> 05:34.682
And then some.

05:34.684 --> 05:38.920
I had someone like that once.

05:42.774 --> 05:44.859
(sighing): And as much
as I'd like to over-share,

05:44.861 --> 05:46.160
I have rounds.

05:46.162 --> 05:48.079
Um, the doctor
will be in shortly.

05:48.081 --> 05:49.413
Hang in there.

05:49.415 --> 05:50.865
Thanks.

05:53.168 --> 05:55.402
(phone vibrating, buzzing)

06:04.263 --> 06:06.764
TESS (over phone):
Cat, I'm so sorry.

06:06.766 --> 06:08.432
I just got the message.

06:08.434 --> 06:10.268
I should have
been there for you.

06:10.270 --> 06:13.754
I'm on my way now with John
Hughes movies and Red Vines.

06:18.143 --> 06:19.360
Vincent.

06:19.362 --> 06:23.097
What if someone sees you?

06:23.099 --> 06:24.949
Playing doctor is
kind of in my wheelhouse.

06:25.984 --> 06:28.602
Besides, I, uh...

06:30.322 --> 06:31.789
I needed to see you.

06:32.874 --> 06:35.009
Thank you.

06:35.011 --> 06:37.278
My nurse told me about that
procedure you did.

06:37.280 --> 06:39.297
Yeah, uh, about that...

06:39.299 --> 06:42.233
The amazing roadside save.

06:42.235 --> 06:43.918
Catherine, uh...

06:43.920 --> 06:45.553
Vincent,
I'm alive because of you.

06:45.555 --> 06:47.571
It wasn't me.

06:47.573 --> 06:51.792
It was, uh,
it was Evan, actually.

06:51.794 --> 06:54.578
I, uh, I just ripped the car
door off, I got you out,

06:54.580 --> 06:58.316
and, I wanted to stay,
uh, to help.

06:58.318 --> 07:03.638
But, I just... I couldn't, you
know, get back to... being me.

07:03.640 --> 07:07.308
And, uh, Evan pulled up,
so I had to make a choice.

07:07.310 --> 07:09.277
He was your best option.

07:09.279 --> 07:12.280
You still saved my life.

07:12.282 --> 07:14.282
If you hadn't got me
out of that car,

07:14.284 --> 07:17.501
Evan never would have
gotten to me in time.

07:17.503 --> 07:20.571
Well, if he hadn't shown
up though, then what?

07:20.573 --> 07:25.042
Sure, I can pull a car door off,
but you needed a doctor and...

07:26.628 --> 07:28.629
I couldn't help you,
you know.

07:28.631 --> 07:33.217
In that moment, all I could do
was... watch you slip away.

07:39.191 --> 07:42.276
You know,
I thought that I lost you.

07:42.278 --> 07:45.813
You didn't lose me.

07:45.815 --> 07:48.582
I'm right here.

07:50.185 --> 07:56.574
And... I accept
all of what you are.

07:56.576 --> 07:58.626
That's what I was
coming to tell you.

07:58.628 --> 08:00.044
I was driving
into the city.

08:00.046 --> 08:02.296
Even though
your DNA is changing,

08:02.298 --> 08:06.317
that doesn't have to change
things between us.

08:06.319 --> 08:08.336
You know you say that now,

08:08.338 --> 08:11.856
but just wait until I sprout
whiskers and a tail.

08:11.858 --> 08:14.041
(phone beeping)

08:18.347 --> 08:19.513
Um...

08:19.515 --> 08:20.898
It's Evan.

08:20.900 --> 08:23.267
He's on his way up.

08:23.269 --> 08:25.403
You know
if I could stay, I would.

08:25.405 --> 08:28.022
I know you would.

08:30.192 --> 08:31.859
Uh...

08:33.160 --> 08:34.662
You should
probably know that Evan

08:34.664 --> 08:36.746
might have seen me
on the road last night.

08:38.450 --> 08:40.251
(whispers):
Okay.

08:43.455 --> 08:45.572
Bye.
Bye.

09:10.816 --> 09:14.402
♪ I'm the blade

09:14.404 --> 09:18.155
♪ You're the knife

09:18.157 --> 09:20.658
♪ I'm a weight

09:20.660 --> 09:23.828
♪ You're the kite...

09:23.830 --> 09:25.129
WOMAN:
Vincent!

09:25.131 --> 09:27.281
♪ Is this my life?

09:27.283 --> 09:28.749
Vincent!

09:28.751 --> 09:31.785
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh...

09:31.787 --> 09:33.254
Vincent Keller!

09:33.256 --> 09:36.557
♪ Am I breathing

09:36.559 --> 09:39.977
♪ Underwater?

09:39.979 --> 09:42.296
♪ Am I breathing

09:42.298 --> 09:45.683
♪ Underwater?

09:50.078 --> 09:54.078
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Beauty and the Beast 1x10 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Seeing Red</font>
